From 53027185705aee19c1d81384478fb178a30ee4b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SN2 Debug <debug@sn2>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 22:54:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] radeon/r100: force full GPU soft reset before CP init for
 unPOSTed cards
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

On platforms without BIOS POST (e.g., SGI Altix SN2), the GPU engines
may be in undefined states causing GUI_ACTIVE (RBBM_STATUS bit 31) to
be permanently set. This makes the CP's ISYNC WAIT_IDLEGUI command
deadlock — the CP reads all ring data successfully (DMA works) but
stalls waiting for GUI idle that never comes.

Evidence from SN2 debugging:
- CP_RB_RPTR=0x20 = CP_RB_WPTR=0x20: CP consumed all ring data
- RBBM_STATUS=0x80010140: GUI_ACTIVE=1, CP_CMDSTRM_BUSY=1
- Ring content: ISYNC with WAIT_IDLEGUI at [0..1], correct encoding
- GART/DMA all working correctly (32-bit ATE-mapped addresses)
- r100_asic_reset() skips reset when GUI_ACTIVE=0 at early init
- RBBM_SOFT_RESET in r100_asic_reset doesn't include SOFT_RESET_CP

Force a full soft reset of all GPU blocks (CP, SE, RE, PP, E2, RB)
immediately before CP initialization to ensure clean engine state.

Includes debug instrumentation to log pre/post reset RBBM_STATUS.
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r100.c | 31 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 31 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r100.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r100.c
index 7bfb0ef..8e54c61 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r100.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/radeon/r100.c
@@ -3987,6 +3987,37 @@ static int r100_startup(struct radeon_device *rdev)
 
 	r100_irq_set(rdev);
 	rdev->config.r100.hdp_cntl = RREG32(RADEON_HOST_PATH_CNTL);
+
+	/* SN2 fix: Force a full soft reset of all GPU blocks before CP init.
+	 * On platforms without BIOS POST (e.g., SGI Altix), the GPU engines
+	 * may be in undefined states causing GUI_ACTIVE to be stuck, which
+	 * makes the CP's ISYNC WAIT_IDLEGUI command deadlock.
+	 * [Evidence: RBBM_STATUS=0x80010140 with GUI_ACTIVE=1 at ring test,
+	 *  CP consumed all ring data (RPTR=WPTR=0x20) but stalled on ISYNC]
+	 */
+	{
+		u32 rbbm_status = RREG32(R_000E40_RBBM_STATUS);
+		printk(KERN_INFO "[SN2-DBG] r100_startup: pre-CP RBBM_STATUS=0x%08x\n", rbbm_status); // [DEBUG INSTRUMENTATION]
+		if (G_000E40_GUI_ACTIVE(rbbm_status)) {
+			printk(KERN_INFO "[SN2-DBG] r100_startup: GUI_ACTIVE set, forcing full soft reset\n"); // [DEBUG INSTRUMENTATION]
+		}
+		/* Reset ALL GPU blocks: CP, SE, RE, PP, E2, RB */
+		WREG32(R_0000F0_RBBM_SOFT_RESET,
+			S_0000F0_SOFT_RESET_CP(1) |
+			S_0000F0_SOFT_RESET_SE(1) |
+			S_0000F0_SOFT_RESET_RE(1) |
+			S_0000F0_SOFT_RESET_PP(1) |
+			S_0000F0_SOFT_RESET_E2(1) |
+			S_0000F0_SOFT_RESET_RB(1));
+		RREG32(R_0000F0_RBBM_SOFT_RESET);
+		mdelay(1);
+		WREG32(R_0000F0_RBBM_SOFT_RESET, 0);
+		RREG32(R_0000F0_RBBM_SOFT_RESET);
+		mdelay(1);
+		rbbm_status = RREG32(R_000E40_RBBM_STATUS);
+		printk(KERN_INFO "[SN2-DBG] r100_startup: post-reset RBBM_STATUS=0x%08x\n", rbbm_status); // [DEBUG INSTRUMENTATION]
+	}
+
 	/* 1M ring buffer */
 	r = r100_cp_init(rdev, 1024 * 1024);
 	if (r) {
-- 
